  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 889faa658c7b2c94ea4fff939bf8022e, type: 3}
  m_Name: DialogNPCItalianKnight
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  Name: 'Paolo Avogadro '
  Icon: {fileID: -834485563, guid: 78d5bbe799641fe43ac5aca0d6572293, type: 3}
  HasInteraction: 0
  interactionType: 3
  Greeting: (Bill 11Labs) Full Speed
  Day1Dialog:
  - "Fort St. Elmo was never meant to stand alone. It exists to defend the entrance
    to the two harbours. It was built to delay \u2014 and thankfully, the Ottomans
    have taken the bait. This buys time for Birgu and Senglea. The longer we hold,
    the greater the chance that the reinforcements promised from Sicily will arrive,
    as the Grand Master was assured."
  Day2FirstTimeDialog:
  - "The fort is built low, which allows them to fire down on us from Mount Sciberras.
    Their volleys never stop \u2014 they fire constantly. The advantage we have is
    that they cannot dig beneath the fortifications due to its position. This fight
    will be decided above the walls, so we must hold them for as long as we can."
  Day2MetBeforeDialog:
  - "The fort is built low, which allows them to fire down on us from Mount Sciberras.
    Their volleys never stop \u2014 they fire constantly. The advantage we have is
    that they cannot dig beneath the fortifications due to its position. This fight
    will be decided above the walls, so we must hold them for as long as we can."
  Day3FirstTimeDialog:
  - "We sent a letter to Grand Master Jean Parisot de Valette. Some asked permission
    to withdraw. His reply was clear: we could return, but fresh troops would take
    our place. No one wished to be remembered as a coward, so we stayed. I know I
    will die here \u2014 but I will die with a sword in my hand."
  Day3MetBeforeDialog:
  - "We sent a letter to Grand Master Jean Parisot de Valette. Some asked permission
    to withdraw. His reply was clear: we could return, but fresh troops would take
    our place. No one wished to be remembered as a coward, so we stayed. I know I
    will die here \u2014 but I will die with a sword in my hand."
  Day4FirstTimeDialog:
  - "The stench is unbearable \u2014 the dead beneath the walls, burning under the
    sun. Be careful out there, boy. Dragut has arrived, and he is a great leader
    among the Ottoman forces. It is his command that has intensified the bombardment.
    They have set up camp on both sides of the fort: Gallows\u2019 Point to the east,
    and Tign\xE9 Point to the west."
  Day4MetBeforeDialog:
  - "The stench is unbearable \u2014 the dead beneath the walls, burning under the
    sun. Be careful out there, boy. Dragut has arrived, and he is a great leader
    among the Ottoman forces. It is his command that has intensified the bombardment.
    They have set up camp on both sides of the fort: Gallows\u2019 Point to the east,
    and Tign\xE9 Point to the west."
  Day5FirstTimeDialog:
  - "We will not abandon this fort. We will fight until the walls fall, or we do.
    St. Elmo must bleed them dry, no matter the cost. If this fort holds, Malta lives.
    If it falls, it will fall with honour. When the walls are breached, I will be
    among the last still standing, sword in hand \u2014 and I will not lower it while
    I still draw breath."
  Day5MetBeforeDialog:
  - "We will not abandon this fort. We will fight until the walls fall, or we do.
    St. Elmo must bleed them dry, no matter the cost. If this fort holds, Malta lives.
    If it falls, it will fall with honour. When the walls are breached, I will be
    among the last still standing, sword in hand \u2014 and I will not lower it while
    I still draw breath."
